race.comment: DADIRRA (9) led and bolted in over the 1300m here last time out, careering away to win by 4.3L in a dominant display. The inside draw may see her up on the speed once again under Nottle and if she can run up to what she did last time out, she'll bring up back-to-back wins. MORE LIKELY (6) has been sound in his trials in town around some lively types since his latest run over 1628m at Geraldton 39 days ago. Back in trip today, but his run two back over this trip at Kalgoorlie was solid. Rates well off that and can feature in the finish once again. DOTHRAKI (3) got the job done two back before a 1.5L defeat over 1100m her last start as the favourite. Drawn well with the rise in trip not being an issue. Can make his presence felt once again. VENTURO (8) is building nicely this time in work and can be coming home with a wet sail. MIDNIGHT RUSH (10) was too good last time out and can feature in the finish.
